==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lave
<hw>Lave</hw> <pr>(l⟦amac⟧v)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Laved</conjf> <pr>(l⟦amac⟧vd)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Laving</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[F. <ets>laver</ets>, L.
<ets>lavare</ets>, akin to <ets>luere</ets> to wash, Gr. <?/. Cf.
<er>Ablution</er>, <er>Deluge</er>, <er>Lavender</er>, <er>Lava</er>,
<er>Lotion</er>.]</ety> <def>To wash; to bathe; <as>as, to <ex>lave</ex>
a bruise</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His feet the foremost breakers <qex>lave</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Byron.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

